Every year, goes to somewhere new! 
My 2014 started in Lombok for a new year party. Got a chance to climb #Kerinci and camp in Thousand island in May. Later on, went to Cisadon village to do charity. In mid year, went to Pramuka and Pari island to dive. I went to Tebing keraton in Aug. Dive in Nusa lembongan, #Bali on my birthday. Then went to Lombok again for a business trip. Next was 15k trail run at Sarwarna beach.

And Finally, I'm going to close this year and start 2015 in #Europe. Especially #Paris.

IKEBANA 
More than simply putting flowers in a container, ikebana is a disciplined art form in which nature and humanity are brought together. Contrary to the idea of floral arrangement as a collection of particolored or multicolored arrangement of blooms, ikebana often emphasizes other areas of the plant, such as its stems and leaves, and draws emphasis toward shape, line, form. Though ikebana is a creative expression, it has certain rules governing its form. The artist's intention behind each arrangement is shown through a piece's color combinations, natural shapes, graceful lines, and the usually implied meaning of the arrangement. #wikipedia

My Christmas present to myself came early: The photobook which I pieced together on Blurb came in the mail today, and I am stoked on life. Physical photo albums (and printing out pictures in general) became phased out in my household ever since I got my first digital camera in the early 00's (aka Facebook early days), so this was my attempt to bring some tactile/visual resonance back. I'd been blessed with a year full of travel, and this is a personal curation of some of my favourite places, moments, stories, and experiences in these locales. Hoping this is my first of many compilations!

Is not this a true autumn day? Just the still melancholy that I love - that makes life and nature harmonise. The birds are consulting about their migrations, the trees are putting on the hectic or the pallid hues of decay, and begin to strew the ground, that one's very footsteps may not disturb the repose of earth and air, while they give us a scent that is a perfect anodyne to the restless spirit. Delicious autumn! My very soul is wedded to it, and if I were a bird I would fly about the earth seeking the successive autumns." [Letter to Miss Eliot, Oct. 1, 1841]  George Eliot

Day13 of #24travelmoments : This is indeed one of the scariest and depressing place I have ever been. At first, I don't even have the guts to look at my photos or any plans to post it online, but then I think that I should let the world see it and know about it. #S21 has been the security prison during the Khmer Rouge, but is now a museum and gallery about the past. Even they have cleaned the place, yet you can still see the horror and hear the screams of the people who were once detained in the area. People must know about this, and we must learn from it. We must not let the history repeat itself. | Tuol Sleng Genocide Museum, November 2014 #24travelmoments @veerabianca
